subSubSection.paragraph:
Thorax
: Pronotum (
Fig. 17
) wider than long, widest at anterior third, narrowest at base. Intervals between punctures slightly narrower than puncture diameter. Scutellar impression (
Fig. 21
) 1.3 times longer than wide, shaped as broadly emarginated inverted triangle, with moderate pubescence. Elytra slightly wider than pronotum, each elytron with deep diagonal groove in apical third.

Abdomen
: Male sternite VIII (
Fig. 25
) wider than long and slightly prolonged apically. Posterior margin of female sternite VIII (
Fig. 29
) broadly round.

Aedeagus (
Figs. 33, 37
) oval, parameres broad, wrapping around the middle of median lobe.

Spermatheca (
Fig. 41
) in the middle curved about 90 degrees.
